292  /*
293  Implementation of two C++17 constructs: conjunction, negation. This is needed
294  to avoid evaluating all the traits in a condition
295 
296  For example: not std::is_same<void, T>::value and has_value_type<T>::value
297  will not compile when T = void (on MSVC at least). Whereas
298  conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, T>>, has_value_type<T>>::value will
299  stop evaluating if negation<...>::value == false
300 
301  Please note that those constructs must be used with caution, since symbols can
302  become very long quickly (which can slow down compilation and cause MSVC
303  internal compiler errors). Only use it when you have to (see example ahead).
304  */
305  template <class...>
306  struct conjunction : std::true_type {};
307  template <class B1>
308  struct conjunction<B1> : B1 {};
309  template <class B1, class... Bn>
310  struct conjunction<B1, Bn...> : std::conditional<bool(B1::value), conjunction<Bn...>, B1>::type {};
311 
312  template <class B>
313  struct negation : std::integral_constant<bool, not B::value> {};
314 
315  // dispatch utility (taken from ranges-v3)
316  template <unsigned N>
317  struct priority_tag : priority_tag<N - 1> {};
318  template <>
319  struct priority_tag<0> {};

338  template <bool B, class RealType, class CompatibleObjectType>
339  struct is_compatible_object_type_impl : std::false_type {};
340 
341  template <class RealType, class CompatibleObjectType>
342  struct is_compatible_object_type_impl<true, RealType, CompatibleObjectType> {
343  static constexpr auto value =
344  std::is_constructible<typename RealType::key_type, typename CompatibleObjectType::key_type>::value and
345  std::is_constructible<typename RealType::mapped_type, typename CompatibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value;
346  };

348  template <class BasicJsonType, class CompatibleObjectType>
349  struct is_compatible_object_type {
350  static auto constexpr value = is_compatible_object_type_impl<
351  conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, CompatibleObjectType>>, has_mapped_type<CompatibleObjectType>,
352  has_key_type<CompatibleObjectType>>::value,
353  typename BasicJsonType::object_t, CompatibleObjectType>::value;
354  };
355 
356  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
357  struct is_basic_json_nested_type {
358  static auto constexpr value = std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::iterator>::value or
359  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::const_iterator>::value or
360  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::reverse_iterator>::value or
361  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::const_reverse_iterator>::value;
362  };
363 
364  template <class BasicJsonType, class CompatibleArrayType>
365  struct is_compatible_array_type {
366  static auto constexpr value =
367  conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, CompatibleArrayType>>,
368  negation<is_compatible_object_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>>,
369  negation<std::is_constructible<typename BasicJsonType::string_t, CompatibleArrayType>>,
370  negation<is_basic_json_nested_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>>,
371  has_value_type<CompatibleArrayType>, has_iterator<CompatibleArrayType>>::value;
372  };

374  template <bool, typename, typename>
375  struct is_compatible_integer_type_impl : std::false_type {};
376 
377  template <typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
378  struct is_compatible_integer_type_impl<true, RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType> {
379  // is there an assert somewhere on overflows?
380  using RealLimits = std::numeric_limits<RealIntegerType>;
381  using CompatibleLimits = std::numeric_limits<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>;
382 
383  static constexpr auto value = std::is_constructible<RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
384  CompatibleLimits::is_integer and
385  RealLimits::is_signed == CompatibleLimits::is_signed;
386  };
387 
388  template <typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
389  struct is_compatible_integer_type {
390  static constexpr auto value = is_compatible_integer_type_impl <
391  std::is_integral<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
392  not std::is_same<bool, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value,
393  RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType > ::value;
394  };

396  // trait checking if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&, udt&) exists
397  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
398  struct has_from_json {
399  private:
400  // also check the return type of from_json
401  template <typename U, typename = enable_if_t<
402  std::is_same<void, decltype(uncvref_t<U>::from_json(std::declval<BasicJsonType>(),
403  std::declval<T &>()))>::value>>
404  static int detect(U &&);
405  static void detect(...);
406 
407  public:
408  static constexpr bool value = std::is_integral<decltype(
409  detect(std::declval<typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>>()))>::value;
410  };

504  class exception : public std::exception {
505  public:

508  return m.what();

514  protected:
515  exception(int id_, const char *what_arg) : id(id_), m(what_arg) {

517 
518  static std::string name(const std::string &ename, int id_) {
519  return "[json.exception." + ename + "." + std::to_string(id_) + "] ";
520  }
521 
522  private:
524  std::runtime_error m;
525  };

587  class parse_error : public exception {
588  public:
597  static parse_error create(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const std::string &what_arg) {

855 
856 namespace nlohmann {
857  namespace detail {
859  // JSON type enumeration //
861 
886  enum class value_t : std::uint8_t {
887  null,
888  object,
889  array,
890  string,
891  boolean,
892  number_integer,
893  number_unsigned,
894  number_float,
895  discarded
896  };
897 
908  inline bool operator<(const value_t lhs, const value_t rhs) noexcept {
909  static constexpr std::array<std::uint8_t, 8> order = {{
910  0 /* null */, 3 /* object */, 4 /* array */, 5 /* string */, 1 /* boolean */, 2 /* integer */,
911  2 /* unsigned */, 2 /* float */
912  }};
913 
914  const auto l_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(lhs);
915  const auto r_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(rhs);
916  return l_index < order.size() and r_index < order.size() and order[l_index] < order[r_index];
917  }
918  }
919 }

940 // #include <nlohmann/detail/value_t.hpp>
941 
942 namespace nlohmann {
943  namespace detail {
944  // overloads for basic_json template parameters
945  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
946  enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
947  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
948  int> = 0>
949  void get_arithmetic_value(const BasicJsonType &j, ArithmeticType &val) {
950  switch (static_cast<value_t>(j)) {
951  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
952  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t *>());
953  break;
954  }
955  case value_t::number_integer: {
956  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t *>());
957  break;
958  }
959  case value_t::number_float: {
960  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t *>());
961  break;
962  }
963 
964  default:
965  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
966  }
967  }
968 
969  template <typename BasicJsonType>
970  void from_json(const BasicJsonType &j, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t &b) {
971  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_boolean())) {
972  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be boolean, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
973  }
974  b = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t *>();
975  }
976 
977  template <typename BasicJsonType>
978  void from_json(const BasicJsonType &j, typename BasicJsonType::string_t &s) {
979  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_string())) {
980  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be string, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
981  }
982  s = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::string_t *>();
983  }
984 
985  template <typename BasicJsonType>
986  void from_json(const BasicJsonType &j, typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t &val) {
987  get_arithmetic_value(j, val);
988  }
989 
990  template <typename BasicJsonType>
991  void from_json(const BasicJsonType &j, typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t &val) {
992  get_arithmetic_value(j, val);
993  }
994 
995  template <typename BasicJsonType>
996  void from_json(const BasicJsonType &j, typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t &val) {
997  get_arithmetic_value(j, val);
998  }
999 
1000  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename EnumType, enable_if_t<std::is_enum<EnumType>::value, int> = 0>
1001  void from_json(const BasicJsonType &j, EnumType &e) {
1002  typename std::underlying_type<EnumType>::type val;
1003  get_arithmetic_value(j, val);
1004  e = static_cast<EnumType>(val);
1005  }
1006 
1007  template <typename BasicJsonType>
1008  void from_json(const BasicJsonType &j, typename BasicJsonType::array_t &arr) {
1009  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array())) {
1010  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1011  }
1012  arr = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::array_t *>();
1013  }
1014 
1015  // forward_list doesn't have an insert method
1016  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename Allocator,
1017  enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
1018  void from_json(const BasicJsonType &j, std::forward_list<T, Allocator> &l) {
1019  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array())) {
1020  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1021  }
1022  std::transform(j.rbegin(), j.rend(), std::front_inserter(l),
1023  [](const BasicJsonType &i) { return i.template get<T>(); });
1024  }
1025 
1026  // valarray doesn't have an insert method
1027  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
1028  void from_json(const BasicJsonType &j, std::valarray<T> &l) {
1029  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array())) {
1030  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1031  }
1032  l.resize(j.size());
1033  std::copy(j.m_value.array->begin(), j.m_value.array->end(), std::begin(l));
1034  }
1035 
1036  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
1037  void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType &j, CompatibleArrayType &arr, priority_tag<0> /*unused*/) {
1038  using std::end;
1039 
1040  std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(), std::inserter(arr, end(arr)), [](const BasicJsonType &i) {
1041  // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
1042  // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
1043  return i.template get<typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>();
1044  });
1045  }
1046 
1047  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
1048  auto from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType &j, CompatibleArrayType &arr, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/)
1049  -> decltype(arr.reserve(std::declval<typename CompatibleArrayType::size_type>()), void()) {
1050  using std::end;
1051 
1052  arr.reserve(j.size());
1053  std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(), std::inserter(arr, end(arr)), [](const BasicJsonType &i) {
1054  // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
1055  // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
1056  return i.template get<typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>();
1057  });
1058  }
1059 
1060  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, std::size_t N>
1061  void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType &j, std::array<T, N> &arr, priority_tag<2> /*unused*/) {
1062  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < N; ++i) {
1063  arr[i] = j.at(i).template get<T>();
1064  }
1065  }
1066 
1067  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType,
1068  enable_if_t<is_compatible_array_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>::value and
1069  std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>::value and
1070  not std::is_same<typename BasicJsonType::array_t, CompatibleArrayType>::value,
1071  int> = 0>
1072  void from_json(const BasicJsonType &j, CompatibleArrayType &arr) {
1073  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array())) {
1074  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1075  }
1076 
1077  from_json_array_impl(j, arr, priority_tag<2>{});
1078  }
1079 
1080  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType,
1081  enable_if_t<is_compatible_object_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleObjectType>::value, int> = 0>
1082  void from_json(const BasicJsonType &j, CompatibleObjectType &obj) {
1083  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_object())) {
1084  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be object, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1085  }
1086 
1087  auto inner_object = j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::object_t *>();
1088  using value_type = typename CompatibleObjectType::value_type;
1089  std::transform(inner_object->begin(), inner_object->end(), std::inserter(obj, obj.begin()),
1090  [](typename BasicJsonType::object_t::value_type const &p) {
1091  return value_type(p.first, p.second.template get<typename CompatibleObjectType::mapped_type>());
1092  });
1093  }
1094 
1095  // overload for arithmetic types, not chosen for basic_json template arguments
1096  // (BooleanType, etc..); note: Is it really necessary to provide explicit
1097  // overloads for boolean_t etc. in case of a custom BooleanType which is not
1098  // an arithmetic type?
1099  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
1100  enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
1101  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t>::value and
1102  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t>::value and
1103  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t>::value and
1104  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
1105  int> = 0>
1106  void from_json(const BasicJsonType &j, ArithmeticType &val) {
1107  switch (static_cast<value_t>(j)) {
1108  case value_t::number_unsigned: {
1109  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t *>());
1110  break;
1111  }
1112  case value_t::number_integer: {
1113  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t *>());
1114  break;
1115  }
1116  case value_t::number_float: {
1117  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t *>());
1118  break;
1119  }
1120  case value_t::boolean: {
1121  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t *>());
1122  break;
1123  }
1124 
1125  default:
1126  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1127  }
1128  }
1129 
1130  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename A1, typename A2>
1131  void from_json(const BasicJsonType &j, std::pair<A1, A2> &p) {
1132  p = {j.at(0).template get<A1>(), j.at(1).template get<A2>()};
1133  }
1134 
1135  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename Tuple, std::size_t... Idx>
1136  void from_json_tuple_impl(const BasicJsonType &j, Tuple &t, index_sequence<Idx...>) {
1137  t = std::make_tuple(j.at(Idx).template get<typename std::tuple_element<Idx, Tuple>::type>()...);
1138  }
1139 
1140  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename... Args>
1141  void from_json(const BasicJsonType &j, std::tuple<Args...> &t) {
1142  from_json_tuple_impl(j, t, index_sequence_for<Args...>{});
1143  }
1144 
1145  struct from_json_fn {
1146  private:
1147  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1148  auto call(const BasicJsonType &j, T &val, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/) const noexcept(noexcept(from_json(j, val)))
1149  -> decltype(from_json(j, val), void()) {
1150  return from_json(j, val);
1151  }
1152 
1153  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1154  void call(const BasicJsonType & /*unused*/, T & /*unused*/, priority_tag<0> /*unused*/) const noexcept {
1155  static_assert(sizeof(BasicJsonType) == 0, "could not find from_json() method in T's namespace");
1156 #ifdef _MSC_VER
1157  // MSVC does not show a stacktrace for the above assert
1158  using decayed = uncvref_t<T>;
1159  static_assert(sizeof(typename decayed::force_msvc_stacktrace) == 0,
1160  "forcing MSVC stacktrace to show which T we're talking about.");
1161 #endif
1162  }
1163 
1164  public:
1165  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1166  void operator()(const BasicJsonType &j, T &val) const
1167  noexcept(noexcept(std::declval<from_json_fn>().call(j, val, priority_tag<1>{}))) {
1168  return call(j, val, priority_tag<1>{});
1169  }
1170  };
1171  }
1172 
1176  namespace {
1177  constexpr const auto &from_json = detail::static_const<detail::from_json_fn>::value;
1178  }
1179 }

1277  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType,
1278  enable_if_t<not std::is_same<CompatibleArrayType, typename BasicJsonType::array_t>::value, int> = 0>
1279  static void construct(BasicJsonType &j, const CompatibleArrayType &arr) {
1280  using std::begin;
1281  using std::end;
1282  j.m_type = value_t::array;
1283  j.m_value.array = j.template create<typename BasicJsonType::array_t>(begin(arr), end(arr));
1284  j.assert_invariant();

1287  template <typename BasicJsonType>
1288  static void construct(BasicJsonType &j, const std::vector<bool> &arr) {
1289  j.m_type = value_t::array;
1290  j.m_value = value_t::array;
1291  j.m_value.array->reserve(arr.size());
1292  for (const bool x : arr) {
1293  j.m_value.array->push_back(x);
1294  }
1295  j.assert_invariant();
1296  }
1297 
1298  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<T, BasicJsonType>::value, int> = 0>
1299  static void construct(BasicJsonType &j, const std::valarray<T> &arr) {
1300  j.m_type = value_t::array;
1301  j.m_value = value_t::array;
1302  j.m_value.array->resize(arr.size());
1303  std::copy(std::begin(arr), std::end(arr), j.m_value.array->begin());
1304  j.assert_invariant();
1305  }
1306  };

1443  struct to_json_fn {
1444  private:
1445  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1446  auto call(BasicJsonType &j, T &&val, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/) const
1447  noexcept(noexcept(to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val)))) -> decltype(to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val)), void()) {
1448  return to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val));
1449  }
1450 
1451  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1452  void call(BasicJsonType & /*unused*/, T && /*unused*/, priority_tag<0> /*unused*/) const noexcept {
1453  static_assert(sizeof(BasicJsonType) == 0, "could not find to_json() method in T's namespace");
1454 
1455 #ifdef _MSC_VER
1456  // MSVC does not show a stacktrace for the above assert
1457  using decayed = uncvref_t<T>;
1458  static_assert(sizeof(typename decayed::force_msvc_stacktrace) == 0,
1459  "forcing MSVC stacktrace to show which T we're talking about.");
1460 #endif
1461  }
1462 
1463  public:
1464  template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1465  void operator()(BasicJsonType &j, T &&val) const
1466  noexcept(noexcept(std::declval<to_json_fn>().call(j, std::forward<T>(val), priority_tag<1>{}))) {
1467  return call(j, std::forward<T>(val), priority_tag<1>{});
1468  }
1469  };
1470  }

1497  namespace detail {
1499  // input adapters //
1501 
1513  struct input_adapter_protocol {
1515  virtual std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() = 0;
1517  virtual void unget_character() = 0;
1518  virtual ~input_adapter_protocol() = default;
1519  };
1520 
1522  using input_adapter_t = std::shared_ptr<input_adapter_protocol>;
1523 
1533  class input_stream_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol {
1534  public:
1535  ~input_stream_adapter() override {
1536  // clear stream flags; we use underlying streambuf I/O, do not
1537  // maintain ifstream flags
1538  is.clear();
1539  }
1540 
1541  explicit input_stream_adapter(std::istream &i) : is(i), sb(*i.rdbuf()) {
1542  // skip byte order mark
1543  std::char_traits<char>::int_type c;
1544  if ((c = get_character()) == 0xEF) {
1545  if ((c = get_character()) == 0xBB) {
1546  if ((c = get_character()) == 0xBF) {
1547  return; // Ignore BOM
1548  } else if (c != std::char_traits<char>::eof()) {
1549  is.unget();
1550  }
1551  is.putback('\xBB');
1552  } else if (c != std::char_traits<char>::eof()) {
1553  is.unget();
1554  }
1555  is.putback('\xEF');
1556  } else if (c != std::char_traits<char>::eof()) {
1557  is.unget(); // no byte order mark; process as usual
1558  }
1559  }
1560 
1561  // delete because of pointer members
1562  input_stream_adapter(const input_stream_adapter &) = delete;
1563  input_stream_adapter &operator=(input_stream_adapter &) = delete;
1564 
1565  // std::istream/std::streambuf use std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type, to
1566  // ensure that std::char_traits<char>::eof() and the character 0xFF do not
1567  // end up as the same value, eg. 0xFFFFFFFF.
1568  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() override {
1569  return sb.sbumpc();
1570  }
1571 
1572  void unget_character() override {
1573  sb.sungetc(); // is.unget() avoided for performance
1574  }
1575 
1576  private:
1578  std::istream &is;
1579  std::streambuf &sb;
1580  };
1581 
1583  class input_buffer_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol {
1584  public:
1585  input_buffer_adapter(const char *b, const std::size_t l) : cursor(b), limit(b + l), start(b) {
1586  // skip byte order mark
1587  if (l >= 3 and b[0] == '\xEF' and b[1] == '\xBB' and b[2] == '\xBF') {
1588  cursor += 3;
1589  }
1590  }
1591 
1592  // delete because of pointer members
1593  input_buffer_adapter(const input_buffer_adapter &) = delete;
1594  input_buffer_adapter &operator=(input_buffer_adapter &) = delete;
1595 
1596  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() noexcept override {
1597  if (JSON_LIKELY(cursor < limit)) {
1598  return std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type(*(cursor++));
1599  }
1600 
1601  return std::char_traits<char>::eof();
1602  }
1603 
1604  void unget_character() noexcept override {
1605  if (JSON_LIKELY(cursor > start)) {
1606  --cursor;
1607  }
1608  }
1609 
1610  private:
1612  const char *cursor;
1614  const char *limit;
1616  const char *start;
1617  };
1618 
1619  class input_adapter {
1620  public:
1621  // native support
1622 
1624  input_adapter(std::istream &i) : ia(std::make_shared<input_stream_adapter>(i)) {
1625  }
1626 
1628  input_adapter(std::istream &&i) : ia(std::make_shared<input_stream_adapter>(i)) {
1629  }
1630 
1632  template <typename CharT,
1633  typename std::enable_if<std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
1634  std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
1635  sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
1636  int>::type = 0>
1637  input_adapter(CharT b, std::size_t l)
1638  : ia(std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(b), l)) {
1639  }
1640 
1641  // derived support
1642 
1644  template <typename CharT,
1645  typename std::enable_if<std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
1646  std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
1647  sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
1648  int>::type = 0>
1649  input_adapter(CharT b)
1650  : input_adapter(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(b), std::strlen(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(b))) {
1651  }
1652 
1654  template <class IteratorType,
1655  typename std::enable_if<std::is_same<typename std::iterator_traits<IteratorType>::iterator_category,
1656  std::random_access_iterator_tag>::value,
1657  int>::type = 0>
1658  input_adapter(IteratorType first, IteratorType last) {
1659  // assertion to check that the iterator range is indeed contiguous,
1660  // see http://stackoverflow.com/a/35008842/266378 for more discussion
1661  assert(std::accumulate(first, last, std::pair<bool, int>(true, 0), [&first](std::pair<bool, int> res,
1662  decltype(*first) val) {
1663  res.first &= (val == *(std::next(std::addressof(*first), res.second++)));
1664  return res;
1665  }).first);
1666 
1667  // assertion to check that each element is 1 byte long
1668  static_assert(sizeof(typename std::iterator_traits<IteratorType>::value_type) == 1,
1669  "each element in the iterator range must have the size of 1 byte");
1670 
1671  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(std::distance(first, last));
1672  if (JSON_LIKELY(len > 0)) {
1673  // there is at least one element: use the address of first
1674  ia = std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&(*first)), len);
1675  } else {
1676  // the address of first cannot be used: use nullptr
1677  ia = std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(nullptr, len);
1678  }
1679  }
1680 
1682  template <class T, std::size_t N>
1683  input_adapter(T (&array)[N]) : input_adapter(std::begin(array), std::end(array)) {
1684  }
1685 
1687  template <class ContiguousContainer,
1688  typename std::enable_if<
1689  not std::is_pointer<ContiguousContainer>::value and
1690  std::is_base_of<std::random_access_iterator_tag,
1691  typename std::iterator_traits<decltype(std::begin(
1692  std::declval<ContiguousContainer const>()))>::iterator_category>::value,
1693  int>::type = 0>
1694  input_adapter(const ContiguousContainer &c) : input_adapter(std::begin(c), std::end(c)) {
1695  }
1696 
1697  operator input_adapter_t() {
1698  return ia;
1699  }
1700 
1701  private:
1703  input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
1704  };
1705  }
1706 }

1735  template <typename BasicJsonType>
1736  class lexer {
1737  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
1738  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
1739  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
1740 
1741  public:
1743  enum class token_type {
1744  uninitialized,
1745  literal_true,
1746  literal_false,
1747  literal_null,
1748  value_string,
1749  value_unsigned,
1750  value_integer,
1751  value_float,
1752  begin_array,
1753  begin_object,
1754  end_array,
1755  end_object,
1756  name_separator,
1757  value_separator,
1758  parse_error,
1759  end_of_input,
1760  literal_or_value
1761  };
1762 
1764  static const char *token_type_name(const token_type t) noexcept {
1765  switch (t) {
1766  case token_type::uninitialized:
1767  return "<uninitialized>";
1768  case token_type::literal_true:
1769  return "true literal";
1770  case token_type::literal_false:
1771  return "false literal";
1772  case token_type::literal_null:
1773  return "null literal";
1774  case token_type::value_string:
1775  return "string literal";
1776  case lexer::token_type::value_unsigned:
1777  case lexer::token_type::value_integer:
1778  case lexer::token_type::value_float:
1779  return "number literal";
1780  case token_type::begin_array:
1781  return "'['";
1782  case token_type::begin_object:
1783  return "'{'";
1784  case token_type::end_array:
1785  return "']'";
1786  case token_type::end_object:
1787  return "'}'";
1788  case token_type::name_separator:
1789  return "':'";
1790  case token_type::value_separator:
1791  return "','";
1792  case token_type::parse_error:
1793  return "<parse error>";
1794  case token_type::end_of_input:
1795  return "end of input";
1796  case token_type::literal_or_value:
1797  return "'[', '{', or a literal";
1798  default: // catch non-enum values
1799  return "unknown token"; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
1800  }
1801  }
1802 
1803  explicit lexer(detail::input_adapter_t adapter)
1804  : ia(std::move(adapter)), decimal_point_char(get_decimal_point()) {
1805  }
1806 
1807  // delete because of pointer members
1808  lexer(const lexer &) = delete;
1809  lexer &operator=(lexer &) = delete;
1810 
1811  private:
1813  // locales
1815 
1817  static char get_decimal_point() noexcept {
1818  const auto loc = localeconv();
1819  assert(loc != nullptr);
1820  return (loc->decimal_point == nullptr) ? '.' : *(loc->decimal_point);
1821  }
1822 
1824  // scan functions
1826 
1842  int get_codepoint() {
1843  // this function only makes sense after reading `\u`
1844  assert(current == 'u');
1845  int codepoint = 0;
1846 
1847  const auto factors = {12, 8, 4, 0};
1848  for (const auto factor : factors) {
1849  get();
1850 
1851  if (current >= '0' and current <= '9') {
1852  codepoint += ((current - 0x30) << factor);
1853  } else if (current >= 'A' and current <= 'F') {
1854  codepoint += ((current - 0x37) << factor);
1855  } else if (current >= 'a' and current <= 'f') {
1856  codepoint += ((current - 0x57) << factor);
1857  } else {
1858  return -1;
1859  }
1860  }
1861 
1862  assert(0x0000 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0xFFFF);
1863  return codepoint;
1864  }
1865 
1881  bool next_byte_in_range(std::initializer_list<int> ranges) {
1882  assert(ranges.size() == 2 or ranges.size() == 4 or ranges.size() == 6);
1883  add(current);
1884 
1885  for (auto range = ranges.begin(); range != ranges.end(); ++range) {
1886  get();
1887  if (JSON_LIKELY(*range <= current and current <= *(++range))) {
1888  add(current);
1889  } else {
1890  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
1891  return false;
1892  }
1893  }
1894 
1895  return true;
1896  }
1897 
1913  token_type scan_string() {
1914  // reset token_buffer (ignore opening quote)
1915  reset();
1916 
1917  // we entered the function by reading an open quote
1918  assert(current == '\"');
1919 
1920  while (true) {
1921  // get next character
1922  switch (get()) {
1923  // end of file while parsing string
1924  case std::char_traits<char>::eof(): {
1925  error_message = "invalid string: missing closing quote";
1926  return token_type::parse_error;
1927  }
1928 
1929  // closing quote
1930  case '\"': {
1931  return token_type::value_string;
1932  }
1933 
1934  // escapes
1935  case '\\': {
1936  switch (get()) {
1937  // quotation mark
1938  case '\"':
1939  add('\"');
1940  break;
1941  // reverse solidus
1942  case '\\':
1943  add('\\');
1944  break;
1945  // solidus
1946  case '/':
1947  add('/');
1948  break;
1949  // backspace
1950  case 'b':
1951  add('\b');
1952  break;
1953  // form feed
1954  case 'f':
1955  add('\f');
1956  break;
1957  // line feed
1958  case 'n':
1959  add('\n');
1960  break;
1961  // carriage return
1962  case 'r':
1963  add('\r');
1964  break;
1965  // tab
1966  case 't':
1967  add('\t');
1968  break;
1969 
1970  // unicode escapes
1971  case 'u': {
1972  const int codepoint1 = get_codepoint();
1973  int codepoint = codepoint1; // start with codepoint1
1974 
1975  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(codepoint1 == -1)) {
1976  error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
1977  return token_type::parse_error;
1978  }
1979 
1980  // check if code point is a high surrogate
1981  if (0xD800 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDBFF) {
1982  // expect next \uxxxx entry
1983  if (JSON_LIKELY(get() == '\\' and get() == 'u')) {
1984  const int codepoint2 = get_codepoint();
1985 
1986  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(codepoint2 == -1)) {
1987  error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
1988  return token_type::parse_error;
1989  }
1990 
1991  // check if codepoint2 is a low surrogate
1992  if (JSON_LIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint2 and codepoint2 <= 0xDFFF)) {
1993  // overwrite codepoint
1994  codepoint =
1995  // high surrogate occupies the most significant 22 bits
1996  (codepoint1 << 10)
1997  // low surrogate occupies the least significant 15 bits
1998  + codepoint2
1999  // there is still the 0xD800, 0xDC00 and 0x10000 noise
2000  // in the result so we have to subtract with:
2001  // (0xD800 << 10) + DC00 - 0x10000 = 0x35FDC00
2002  - 0x35FDC00;
2003  } else {
2004  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
2005  return token_type::parse_error;
2006  }
2007  } else {
2008  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
2009  return token_type::parse_error;
2010  }
2011  } else {
2012  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDFFF)) {
2013  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must follow U+D800..U+DBFF";
2014  return token_type::parse_error;
2015  }
2016  }
2017 
2018  // result of the above calculation yields a proper codepoint
2019  assert(0x00 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0x10FFFF);
2020 
2021  // translate codepoint into bytes
2022  if (codepoint < 0x80) {
2023  // 1-byte characters: 0xxxxxxx (ASCII)
2024  add(codepoint);
2025  } else if (codepoint <= 0x7FF) {
2026  // 2-byte characters: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx
2027  add(0xC0 | (codepoint >> 6));
2028  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
2029  } else if (codepoint <= 0xFFFF) {
2030  // 3-byte characters: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
2031  add(0xE0 | (codepoint >> 12));
2032  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F));
2033  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
2034  } else {
2035  // 4-byte characters: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
2036  add(0xF0 | (codepoint >> 18));
2037  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 12) & 0x3F));
2038  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F));
2039  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
2040  }
2041 
2042  break;
2043  }
2044 
2045  // other characters after escape
2046  default:
2047  error_message = "invalid string: forbidden character after backslash";
2048  return token_type::parse_error;
2049  }
2050 
2051  break;
2052  }
2053 
2054  // invalid control characters
2055  case 0x00:
2056  case 0x01:
2057  case 0x02:
2058  case 0x03:
2059  case 0x04:
2060  case 0x05:
2061  case 0x06:
2062  case 0x07:
2063  case 0x08:
2064  case 0x09:
2065  case 0x0A:
2066  case 0x0B:
2067  case 0x0C:
2068  case 0x0D:
2069  case 0x0E:
2070  case 0x0F:
2071  case 0x10:
2072  case 0x11:
2073  case 0x12:
2074  case 0x13:
2075  case 0x14:
2076  case 0x15:
2077  case 0x16:
2078  case 0x17:
2079  case 0x18:
2080  case 0x19:
2081  case 0x1A:
2082  case 0x1B:
2083  case 0x1C:
2084  case 0x1D:
2085  case 0x1E:
2086  case 0x1F: {
2087  error_message = "invalid string: control character must be escaped";
2088  return token_type::parse_error;
2089  }
2090 
2091  // U+0020..U+007F (except U+0022 (quote) and U+005C (backspace))
2092  case 0x20:
2093  case 0x21:
2094  case 0x23:
2095  case 0x24:
2096  case 0x25:
2097  case 0x26:
2098  case 0x27:
2099  case 0x28:
2100  case 0x29:
2101  case 0x2A:
2102  case 0x2B:
2103  case 0x2C:

2109  case 0x32:

2118  case 0x3B:

2122  case 0x3F:
2123  case 0x40:

2191  case 0xC2:

2195  case 0xC6:
2196  case 0xC7:
2197  case 0xC8:

2208  case 0xD3:

2228  case 0xE0: {
2229  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0xA0, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
2230  return token_type::parse_error;

2235  // U+1000..U+CFFF: bytes E1..EC 80..BF 80..BF
2236  // U+E000..U+FFFF: bytes EE..EF 80..BF 80..BF
2237  case 0xE1:
2238  case 0xE2:
2239  case 0xE3:
2240  case 0xE4:
2241  case 0xE5:
2242  case 0xE6:
2243  case 0xE7:
2244  case 0xE8:
2245  case 0xE9:
2246  case 0xEA:
2247  case 0xEB:
2248  case 0xEC:
2249  case 0xEE:
2250  case 0xEF: {
2251  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
2252  return token_type::parse_error;
2253  }
2254  break;
2255  }
2256 
2257  // U+D000..U+D7FF: bytes ED 80..9F 80..BF
2258  case 0xED: {
2259  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0x9F, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
2260  return token_type::parse_error;
2261  }
2262  break;
2263  }
2264 
2265  // U+10000..U+3FFFF F0 90..BF 80..BF 80..BF
2266  case 0xF0: {
2267  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x90, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
2268  return token_type::parse_error;
2269  }
2270  break;
2271  }
2272 
2273  // U+40000..U+FFFFF F1..F3 80..BF 80..BF 80..BF
2274  case 0xF1:
2275  case 0xF2:
2276  case 0xF3: {
2277  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
2278  return token_type::parse_error;
2279  }
2280  break;
2281  }
2282 
2283  // U+100000..U+10FFFF F4 80..8F 80..BF 80..BF
2284  case 0xF4: {
2285  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0x8F, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF})))) {
2286  return token_type::parse_error;
2287  }
2288  break;
2289  }
2290 
2291  // remaining bytes (80..C1 and F5..FF) are ill-formed
2292  default: {
2293  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
2294  return token_type::parse_error;
2295  }
2296  }
2297  }
2298  }
2299 
2300  static void strtof(float &f, const char *str, char **endptr) noexcept {
2301  f = std::strtof(str, endptr);
2302  }
2303 
2304  static void strtof(double &f, const char *str, char **endptr) noexcept {
2305  f = std::strtod(str, endptr);
2306  }
2307 
2308  static void strtof(long double &f, const char *str, char **endptr) noexcept {
2309  f = std::strtold(str, endptr);
2310  }
2311 
2352  token_type scan_number() {
2353  // reset token_buffer to store the number's bytes
2354  reset();
2355 
2356  // the type of the parsed number; initially set to unsigned; will be
2357  // changed if minus sign, decimal point or exponent is read
2358  token_type number_type = token_type::value_unsigned;
2359 
2360  // state (init): we just found out we need to scan a number
2361  switch (current) {
2362  case '-': {
2363  add(current);
2364  goto scan_number_minus;
2365  }
2366 
2367  case '0': {
2368  add(current);
2369  goto scan_number_zero;
2370  }
2371 
2372  case '1':
2373  case '2':
2374  case '3':
2375  case '4':
2376  case '5':
2377  case '6':
2378  case '7':
2379  case '8':
2380  case '9': {
2381  add(current);
2382  goto scan_number_any1;
2383  }
2384 
2385  default: {
2386  // all other characters are rejected outside scan_number()
2387  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
2388  }
2389  }
2390 
2391  scan_number_minus:
2392  // state: we just parsed a leading minus sign
2393  number_type = token_type::value_integer;
2394  switch (get()) {
2395  case '0': {
2396  add(current);
2397  goto scan_number_zero;
2398  }
2399 
2400  case '1':
2401  case '2':
2402  case '3':
2403  case '4':
2404  case '5':
2405  case '6':
2406  case '7':
2407  case '8':
2408  case '9': {
2409  add(current);
2410  goto scan_number_any1;
2411  }
2412 
2413  default: {
2414  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '-'";
2415  return token_type::parse_error;
2416  }
2417  }
2418 
2419  scan_number_zero:
2420  // state: we just parse a zero (maybe with a leading minus sign)
2421  switch (get()) {
2422  case '.': {
2423  add(decimal_point_char);
2424  goto scan_number_decimal1;
2425  }
2426 
2427  case 'e':
2428  case 'E': {
2429  add(current);
2430  goto scan_number_exponent;
2431  }
2432 
2433  default:
2434  goto scan_number_done;
2435  }
2436 
2437  scan_number_any1:
2438  // state: we just parsed a number 0-9 (maybe with a leading minus sign)
2439  switch (get()) {
2440  case '0':
2441  case '1':
2442  case '2':
2443  case '3':
2444  case '4':
2445  case '5':
2446  case '6':
2447  case '7':
2448  case '8':
2449  case '9': {
2450  add(current);
2451  goto scan_number_any1;
2452  }
2453 
2454  case '.': {
2455  add(decimal_point_char);
2456  goto scan_number_decimal1;
2457  }
2458 
2459  case 'e':
2460  case 'E': {
2461  add(current);
2462  goto scan_number_exponent;
2463  }
2464 
2465  default:
2466  goto scan_number_done;
2467  }
2468 
2469  scan_number_decimal1:
2470  // state: we just parsed a decimal point
2471  number_type = token_type::value_float;
2472  switch (get()) {
2473  case '0':
2474  case '1':
2475  case '2':
2476  case '3':
2477  case '4':
2478  case '5':
2479  case '6':
2480  case '7':
2481  case '8':
2482  case '9': {
2483  add(current);
2484  goto scan_number_decimal2;
2485  }
2486 
2487  default: {
2488  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '.'";
2489  return token_type::parse_error;
2490  }
2491  }
2492 
2493  scan_number_decimal2:
2494  // we just parsed at least one number after a decimal point
2495  switch (get()) {
2496  case '0':
2497  case '1':
2498  case '2':
2499  case '3':
2500  case '4':
2501  case '5':
2502  case '6':
2503  case '7':
2504  case '8':
2505  case '9': {
2506  add(current);
2507  goto scan_number_decimal2;
2508  }
2509 
2510  case 'e':
2511  case 'E': {
2512  add(current);
2513  goto scan_number_exponent;
2514  }
2515 
2516  default:
2517  goto scan_number_done;
2518  }
2519 
2520  scan_number_exponent:
2521  // we just parsed an exponent
2522  number_type = token_type::value_float;
2523  switch (get()) {
2524  case '+':
2525  case '-': {
2526  add(current);
2527  goto scan_number_sign;
2528  }
2529 
2530  case '0':
2531  case '1':
2532  case '2':
2533  case '3':
2534  case '4':
2535  case '5':
2536  case '6':
2537  case '7':
2538  case '8':
2539  case '9': {
2540  add(current);
2541  goto scan_number_any2;
2542  }
2543 
2544  default: {
2545  error_message = "invalid number; expected '+', '-', or digit after exponent";
2546  return token_type::parse_error;
2547  }
2548  }
2549 
2550  scan_number_sign:
2551  // we just parsed an exponent sign
2552  switch (get()) {
2553  case '0':
2554  case '1':
2555  case '2':
2556  case '3':
2557  case '4':
2558  case '5':
2559  case '6':
2560  case '7':
2561  case '8':
2562  case '9': {
2563  add(current);
2564  goto scan_number_any2;
2565  }
2566 
2567  default: {
2568  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after exponent sign";
2569  return token_type::parse_error;
2570  }
2571  }
2572 
2573  scan_number_any2:
2574  // we just parsed a number after the exponent or exponent sign
2575  switch (get()) {
2576  case '0':
2577  case '1':
2578  case '2':
2579  case '3':
2580  case '4':
2581  case '5':
2582  case '6':
2583  case '7':
2584  case '8':
2585  case '9': {
2586  add(current);
2587  goto scan_number_any2;
2588  }
2589 
2590  default:
2591  goto scan_number_done;
2592  }
2593 
2594  scan_number_done:
2595  // unget the character after the number (we only read it to know that
2596  // we are done scanning a number)
2597  unget();
2598 
2599  char *endptr = nullptr;
2600  errno = 0;
2601 
2602  // try to parse integers first and fall back to floats
2603  if (number_type == token_type::value_unsigned) {
2604  const auto x = std::strtoull(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
2605 
2606  // we checked the number format before
2607  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
2608 
2609  if (errno == 0) {
2610  value_unsigned = static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(x);
2611  if (value_unsigned == x) {
2612  return token_type::value_unsigned;
2613  }
2614  }
2615  } else if (number_type == token_type::value_integer) {
2616  const auto x = std::strtoll(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
2617 
2618  // we checked the number format before
2619  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
2620 
2621  if (errno == 0) {
2622  value_integer = static_cast<number_integer_t>(x);
2623  if (value_integer == x) {
2624  return token_type::value_integer;
2625  }
2626  }
2627  }
2628 
2629  // this code is reached if we parse a floating-point number or if an
2630  // integer conversion above failed
2631  strtof(value_float, token_buffer.data(), &endptr);
2632 
2633  // we checked the number format before
2634  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
2635 
2636  return token_type::value_float;
2637  }
2638 
2644  token_type scan_literal(const char *literal_text, const std::size_t length, token_type return_type) {
2645  assert(current == literal_text[0]);
2646  for (std::size_t i = 1; i < length; ++i) {
2647  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get() != literal_text[i])) {
2648  error_message = "invalid literal";
2649  return token_type::parse_error;
2650  }
2651  }
2652  return return_type;
2653  }
2654 
2656  // input management
2658 
2660  void reset() noexcept {
2661  token_buffer.clear();
2662  token_string.clear();
2663  token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(current));
2664  }
2665 
2666  /*
2667  @brief get next character from the input
2668 
2669  This function provides the interface to the used input adapter. It does
2670  not throw in case the input reached EOF, but returns a
2671  `std::char_traits<char>::eof()` in that case. Stores the scanned characters
2672  for use in error messages.
2673 
2674  @return character read from the input
2675  */
2676  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get() {
2677  ++chars_read;
2678  current = ia->get_character();
2679  if (JSON_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof())) {
2680  token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(current));
2681  }
2682  return current;
2683  }
2684 
2686  void unget() {
2687  --chars_read;
2688  if (JSON_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof())) {
2689  ia->unget_character();
2690  assert(token_string.size() != 0);
2691  token_string.pop_back();
2692  }
2693  }
2694 
2696  void add(int c) {
2697  token_buffer.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(c));
2698  }
2699 
2700  public:
2702  // value getters
2704 
2706  constexpr number_integer_t get_number_integer() const noexcept {
2707  return value_integer;
2708  }
2709 
2711  constexpr number_unsigned_t get_number_unsigned() const noexcept {
2712  return value_unsigned;
2713  }
2714 
2716  constexpr number_float_t get_number_float() const noexcept {
2717  return value_float;
2718  }
2719 
2721  std::string move_string() {
2722  return std::move(token_buffer);
2723  }
2724 
2726  // diagnostics
2728 
2730  constexpr std::size_t get_position() const noexcept {
2731  return chars_read;
2732  }
2733 
2737  std::string get_token_string() const {
2738  // escape control characters
2739  std::string result;
2740  for (const auto c : token_string) {
2741  if ('\x00' <= c and c <= '\x1F') {
2742  // escape control characters
2743  std::stringstream ss;
2744  ss << "<U+" << std::setw(4) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << static_cast<int>(c)
2745  << ">";
2746  result += ss.str();
2747  } else {
2748  // add character as is
2749  result.push_back(c);
2750  }
2751  }
2752 
2753  return result;
2754  }
2755 
2757  constexpr const char *get_error_message() const noexcept {
2758  return error_message;
2759  }
2760 
2762  // actual scanner
2764 
2765  token_type scan() {
2766  // read next character and ignore whitespace
2767  do {
2768  get();
2769  } while (current == ' ' or current == '\t' or current == '\n' or current == '\r');
2770 
2771  switch (current) {
2772  // structural characters
2773  case '[':
2774  return token_type::begin_array;
2775  case ']':
2776  return token_type::end_array;
2777  case '{':
2778  return token_type::begin_object;
2779  case '}':
2780  return token_type::end_object;
2781  case ':':
2782  return token_type::name_separator;
2783  case ',':
2784  return token_type::value_separator;
2785 
2786  // literals
2787  case 't':
2788  return scan_literal("true", 4, token_type::literal_true);
2789  case 'f':
2790  return scan_literal("false", 5, token_type::literal_false);
2791  case 'n':
2792  return scan_literal("null", 4, token_type::literal_null);
2793 
2794  // string
2795  case '\"':
2796  return scan_string();
2797 
2798  // number
2799  case '-':
2800  case '0':
2801  case '1':
2802  case '2':
2803  case '3':
2804  case '4':
2805  case '5':
2806  case '6':
2807  case '7':
2808  case '8':
2809  case '9':
2810  return scan_number();
2811 
2812  // end of input (the null byte is needed when parsing from
2813  // string literals)
2814  case '\0':
2815  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
2816  return token_type::end_of_input;
2817 
2818  // error
2819  default:
2820  error_message = "invalid literal";
2821  return token_type::parse_error;
2822  }
2823  }
2824 
2825  private:
2827  detail::input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
2828 
2830  std::char_traits<char>::int_type current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
2831 
2833  std::size_t chars_read = 0;
2834 
2836  std::vector<char> token_string{};
2837 
2839  std::string token_buffer{};
2840 
2842  const char *error_message = "";
2843 
2844  // number values
2845  number_integer_t value_integer = 0;
2846  number_unsigned_t value_unsigned = 0;
2847  number_float_t value_float = 0;
2848 
2850  const char decimal_point_char = '.';
2851  };
2852  }
2853 }

2858 #include <cmath> // isfinite
2859 #include <cstdint> // uint8_t
2860 #include <functional> // function
2861 #include <string> // string
2862 #include <utility> // move
2863 
2864 // #include <nlohmann/detail/exceptions.hpp>
2865 
2866 // #include <nlohmann/detail/macro_scope.hpp>
2867 
2868 // #include <nlohmann/detail/input/input_adapters.hpp>

2872 // #include <nlohmann/detail/value_t.hpp>

2874 namespace nlohmann {
2875  namespace detail {
2877  // parser //
2879 
2885  template <typename BasicJsonType>
2886  class parser {
2887  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
2888  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
2889  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
2890  using lexer_t = lexer<BasicJsonType>;
2891  using token_type = typename lexer_t::token_type;
2892 
2893  public:
2894  enum class parse_event_t : uint8_t {
2896  object_start,
2898  object_end,
2900  array_start,
2902  array_end,
2904  key,
2906  value
2907  };
2908 
2909  using parser_callback_t = std::function<bool(int depth, parse_event_t event, BasicJsonType &parsed)>;
2910 
2912  explicit parser(detail::input_adapter_t adapter, const parser_callback_t cb = nullptr,
2913  const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
2914  : callback(cb), m_lexer(adapter), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_) {
2915  }
2916 
2927  void parse(const bool strict, BasicJsonType &result) {
2928  // read first token
2929  get_token();
2930 
2931  parse_internal(true, result);
2932  result.assert_invariant();
2933 
2934  // in strict mode, input must be completely read
2935  if (strict) {
2936  get_token();
2937  expect(token_type::end_of_input);
2938  }
2939 
2940  // in case of an error, return discarded value
2941  if (errored) {
2942  result = value_t::discarded;
2943  return;
2944  }
2945 
2946  // set top-level value to null if it was discarded by the callback
2947  // function
2948  if (result.is_discarded()) {
2949  result = nullptr;
2950  }
2951  }
2952 
2959  bool accept(const bool strict = true) {
2960  // read first token
2961  get_token();
2962 
2963  if (not accept_internal()) {
2964  return false;
2965  }
2966 
2967  // strict => last token must be EOF
2968  return not strict or (get_token() == token_type::end_of_input);
2969  }
2970 
2971  private:
2978  void parse_internal(bool keep, BasicJsonType &result) {
2979  // never parse after a parse error was detected
2980  assert(not errored);
2981 
2982  // start with a discarded value
2983  if (not result.is_discarded()) {
2984  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
2985  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
2986  }
2987 
2988  switch (last_token) {
2989  case token_type::begin_object: {
2990  if (keep) {
2991  if (callback) {
2992  keep = callback(depth++, parse_event_t::object_start, result);
2993  }
2994 
2995  if (not callback or keep) {
2996  // explicitly set result to object to cope with {}
2997  result.m_type = value_t::object;
2998  result.m_value = value_t::object;
2999  }
3000  }
3001 
3002  // read next token
3003  get_token();
3004 
3005  // closing } -> we are done
3006  if (last_token == token_type::end_object) {
3007  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::object_end, result)) {
3008  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3009  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3010  }
3011  break;
3012  }
3013 
3014  // parse values
3015  std::string key;
3016  BasicJsonType value;
3017  while (true) {
3018  // store key
3019  if (not expect(token_type::value_string)) {
3020  return;
3021  }
3022  key = m_lexer.move_string();
3023 
3024  bool keep_tag = false;
3025  if (keep) {
3026  if (callback) {
3027  BasicJsonType k(key);
3028  keep_tag = callback(depth, parse_event_t::key, k);
3029  } else {
3030  keep_tag = true;
3031  }
3032  }
3033 
3034  // parse separator (:)
3035  get_token();
3036  if (not expect(token_type::name_separator)) {
3037  return;
3038  }
3039 
3040  // parse and add value
3041  get_token();
3042  value.m_value.destroy(value.m_type);
3043  value.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3044  parse_internal(keep, value);
3045 
3046  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(errored)) {
3047  return;
3048  }
3049 
3050  if (keep and keep_tag and not value.is_discarded()) {
3051  result.m_value.object->emplace(std::move(key), std::move(value));
3052  }
3053 
3054  // comma -> next value
3055  get_token();
3056  if (last_token == token_type::value_separator) {
3057  get_token();
3058  continue;
3059  }
3060 
3061  // closing }
3062  if (not expect(token_type::end_object)) {
3063  return;
3064  }
3065  break;
3066  }
3067 
3068  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::object_end, result)) {
3069  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3070  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3071  }
3072  break;
3073  }
3074 
3075  case token_type::begin_array: {
3076  if (keep) {
3077  if (callback) {
3078  keep = callback(depth++, parse_event_t::array_start, result);
3079  }
3080 
3081  if (not callback or keep) {
3082  // explicitly set result to array to cope with []
3083  result.m_type = value_t::array;
3084  result.m_value = value_t::array;
3085  }
3086  }
3087 
3088  // read next token
3089  get_token();
3090 
3091  // closing ] -> we are done
3092  if (last_token == token_type::end_array) {
3093  if (callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::array_end, result)) {
3094  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3095  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3096  }
3097  break;
3098  }
3099 
3100  // parse values
3101  BasicJsonType value;
3102  while (true) {
3103  // parse value
3104  value.m_value.destroy(value.m_type);
3105  value.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3106  parse_internal(keep, value);
3107 
3108  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(errored)) {
3109  return;
3110  }
3111 
3112  if (keep and not value.is_discarded()) {
3113  result.m_value.array->push_back(std::move(value));
3114  }
3115 
3116  // comma -> next value
3117  get_token();
3118  if (last_token == token_type::value_separator) {
3119  get_token();
3120  continue;
3121  }
3122 
3123  // closing ]
3124  if (not expect(token_type::end_array)) {
3125  return;
3126  }
3127  break;
3128  }
3129 
3130  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::array_end, result)) {
3131  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3132  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3133  }
3134  break;
3135  }
3136 
3137  case token_type::literal_null: {
3138  result.m_type = value_t::null;
3139  break;
3140  }
3141 
3142  case token_type::value_string: {
3143  result.m_type = value_t::string;
3144  result.m_value = m_lexer.move_string();
3145  break;
3146  }
3147 
3148  case token_type::literal_true: {
3149  result.m_type = value_t::boolean;
3150  result.m_value = true;
3151  break;
3152  }
3153 
3154  case token_type::literal_false: {
3155  result.m_type = value_t::boolean;
3156  result.m_value = false;
3157  break;
3158  }
3159 
3160  case token_type::value_unsigned: {
3161  result.m_type = value_t::number_unsigned;
3162  result.m_value = m_lexer.get_number_unsigned();
3163  break;
3164  }
3165 
3166  case token_type::value_integer: {
3167  result.m_type = value_t::number_integer;
3168  result.m_value = m_lexer.get_number_integer();
3169  break;
3170  }
3171 
3172  case token_type::value_float: {
3173  result.m_type = value_t::number_float;
3174  result.m_value = m_lexer.get_number_float();
3175 
3176  // throw in case of infinity or NAN
3177  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not std::isfinite(result.m_value.number_float))) {
3178  if (allow_exceptions) {
3179  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(406, "number overflow parsing '" + m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'"));
3180  }
3181  expect(token_type::uninitialized);
3182  }
3183  break;
3184  }
3185 
3186  case token_type::parse_error: {
3187  // using "uninitialized" to avoid "expected" message
3188  if (not expect(token_type::uninitialized)) {
3189  return;
3190  }
3191  break; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3192  }
3193 
3194  default: {
3195  // the last token was unexpected; we expected a value
3196  if (not expect(token_type::literal_or_value)) {
3197  return;
3198  }
3199  break; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3200  }
3201  }
3202 
3203  if (keep and callback and not callback(depth, parse_event_t::value, result)) {
3204  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3205  }
3206  }
3207 
3218  bool accept_internal() {
3219  switch (last_token) {
3220  case token_type::begin_object: {
3221  // read next token
3222  get_token();
3223 
3224  // closing } -> we are done
3225  if (last_token == token_type::end_object) {
3226  return true;
3227  }
3228 
3229  // parse values
3230  while (true) {
3231  // parse key
3232  if (last_token != token_type::value_string) {
3233  return false;
3234  }
3235 
3236  // parse separator (:)
3237  get_token();
3238  if (last_token != token_type::name_separator) {
3239  return false;
3240  }
3241 
3242  // parse value
3243  get_token();
3244  if (not accept_internal()) {
3245  return false;
3246  }
3247 
3248  // comma -> next value
3249  get_token();
3250  if (last_token == token_type::value_separator) {
3251  get_token();
3252  continue;
3253  }
3254 
3255  // closing }
3256  return (last_token == token_type::end_object);
3257  }
3258  }
3259 
3260  case token_type::begin_array: {
3261  // read next token
3262  get_token();
3263 
3264  // closing ] -> we are done
3265  if (last_token == token_type::end_array) {
3266  return true;
3267  }
3268 
3269  // parse values
3270  while (true) {
3271  // parse value
3272  if (not accept_internal()) {
3273  return false;
3274  }
3275 
3276  // comma -> next value
3277  get_token();
3278  if (last_token == token_type::value_separator) {
3279  get_token();
3280  continue;
3281  }
3282 
3283  // closing ]
3284  return (last_token == token_type::end_array);
3285  }
3286  }
3287 
3288  case token_type::value_float: {
3289  // reject infinity or NAN
3290  return std::isfinite(m_lexer.get_number_float());
3291  }
3292 
3293  case token_type::literal_false:
3294  case token_type::literal_null:
3295  case token_type::literal_true:
3296  case token_type::value_integer:
3297  case token_type::value_string:
3298  case token_type::value_unsigned:
3299  return true;
3300 
3301  default: // the last token was unexpected
3302  return false;
3303  }
3304  }
3305 
3307  token_type get_token() {
3308  return (last_token = m_lexer.scan());
3309  }
3310 
3314  bool expect(token_type t) {
3315  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(t != last_token)) {
3316  errored = true;
3317  expected = t;
3318  if (allow_exceptions) {
3319  throw_exception();
3320  } else {
3321  return false;
3322  }
3323  }
3324 
3325  return true;
3326  }
3327 
3328  [[noreturn]] void throw_exception() const {
3329  std::string error_msg = "syntax error - ";
3330  if (last_token == token_type::parse_error) {
3331  error_msg += std::string(m_lexer.get_error_message()) + "; last read: '" + m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'";
3332  } else {
3333  error_msg += "unexpected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(last_token));
3334  }
3335 
3336  if (expected != token_type::uninitialized) {
3337  error_msg += "; expected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(expected));
3338  }
3339 
3340  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), error_msg));
3341  }
3342 
3343  private:
3345  int depth = 0;
3347  const parser_callback_t callback = nullptr;
3349  token_type last_token = token_type::uninitialized;
3351  lexer_t m_lexer;
3353  bool errored = false;
3355  token_type expected = token_type::uninitialized;
3357  const bool allow_exceptions = true;
3358  };
3359  }
3360 }
3361 
3362 // #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/primitive_iterator.hpp>
3363 
3364 #include <cstddef> // ptrdiff_t
3365 #include <limits> // numeric_limits
3366 
3367 namespace nlohmann {
3368  namespace detail {
3369  /*
3370  @brief an iterator for primitive JSON types
3371 
3372  This class models an iterator for primitive JSON types (boolean, number,
3373  string). It's only purpose is to allow the iterator/const_iterator classes
3374  to "iterate" over primitive values. Internally, the iterator is modeled by
3375  a `difference_type` variable. Value begin_value (`0`) models the begin,
3376  end_value (`1`) models past the end.
3377  */
3378  class primitive_iterator_t {
3379  private:
3380  using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
3381  static constexpr difference_type begin_value = 0;
3382  static constexpr difference_type end_value = begin_value + 1;
3383 
3385  difference_type m_it = (std::numeric_limits<std::ptrdiff_t>::min)();
3386 
3387  public:
3388  constexpr difference_type get_value() const noexcept {
3389  return m_it;
3390  }
3391 
3393  void set_begin() noexcept {
3394  m_it = begin_value;
3395  }
3396 
3398  void set_end() noexcept {
3399  m_it = end_value;
3400  }
3401 
3403  constexpr bool is_begin() const noexcept {
3404  return m_it == begin_value;
3405  }
3406 
3408  constexpr bool is_end() const noexcept {
3409  return m_it == end_value;
3410  }
3411 
3412  friend constexpr bool operator==(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept {
3413  return lhs.m_it == rhs.m_it;
3414  }
3415 
3416  friend constexpr bool operator<(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept {
3417  return lhs.m_it < rhs.m_it;
3418  }
3419 
3420  primitive_iterator_t operator+(difference_type n) noexcept {
3421  auto result = *this;
3422  result += n;
3423  return result;
3424  }
3425 
3426  friend constexpr difference_type operator-(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept {
3427  return lhs.m_it - rhs.m_it;
3428  }
3429 
3430  primitive_iterator_t &operator++() noexcept {
3431  ++m_it;
3432  return *this;
3433  }
3434 
3435  primitive_iterator_t const operator++(int)noexcept {
3436  auto result = *this;
3437  m_it++;
3438  return result;
3439  }
3440 
3441  primitive_iterator_t &operator--() noexcept {
3442  --m_it;
3443  return *this;
3444  }
3445 
3446  primitive_iterator_t const operator--(int)noexcept {
3447  auto result = *this;
3448  m_it--;
3449  return result;
3450  }
3451 
3452  primitive_iterator_t &operator+=(difference_type n) noexcept {
3453  m_it += n;
3454  return *this;
3455  }
3456 
3457  primitive_iterator_t &operator-=(difference_type n) noexcept {
3458  m_it -= n;
3459  return *this;
3460  }
3461  };
3462  }
3463 }

3484  primitive_iterator_t primitive_iterator{};

3640  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->begin();
3641  break;

3645  m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->begin();
3646  break;

3825  bool operator==(const iter_impl &other) const {
3826  // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
3827  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object)) {
3828  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
3829  }

3832 
3833  switch (m_object->m_type) {
3834  case value_t::object:
3835  return (m_it.object_iterator == other.m_it.object_iterator);
3836 
3837  case value_t::array:
3838  return (m_it.array_iterator == other.m_it.array_iterator);
3839

3841  return (m_it.primitive_iterator == other.m_it.primitive_iterator);

4051  template <typename IteratorType>
4052  class iteration_proxy {
4053  private:
4055  class iteration_proxy_internal {
4056  private:
4058  IteratorType anchor;

4061 
4062  public:
4063  explicit iteration_proxy_internal(IteratorType it) noexcept : anchor(it) {
4064  }
4065 
4067  iteration_proxy_internal &operator*() {
4068  return *this;
4069  }
4070 
4072  iteration_proxy_internal &operator++() {
4073  ++anchor;
4074  ++array_index;
4075 
4076  return *this;
4077  }
4078 
4080  bool operator!=(const iteration_proxy_internal &o) const noexcept {
4081  return anchor != o.anchor;
4082  }
4083 
4085  std::string key() const {
4086  assert(anchor.m_object != nullptr);
4087 
4088  switch (anchor.m_object->type()) {
4089  // use integer array index as key
4090  case value_t::array:
4091  return std::to_string(array_index);
4092 
4093  // use key from the object
4094  case value_t::object:
4095  return anchor.key();
4096 
4097  // use an empty key for all primitive types
4098  default:
4099  return "";
4100  }
4101  }
4102 
4104  typename IteratorType::reference value() const {
4105  return anchor.value();
4106  }
4107  };
4108 
4110  typename IteratorType::reference container;
4111 
4112  public:
4114  explicit iteration_proxy(typename IteratorType::reference cont) noexcept : container(cont) {
4115  }
4116 
4118  iteration_proxy_internal begin() noexcept {
4119  return iteration_proxy_internal(container.begin());
4120  }
4121 
4123  iteration_proxy_internal end() noexcept {
4124  return iteration_proxy_internal(container.end());
4125  }
4126  };
4127  }
4128 }

4167  using reference = typename Base::reference;

4180  }

4185  }

4251  template <typename CharType>
4252  struct output_adapter_protocol {
4253  virtual void write_character(CharType c) = 0;
4254  virtual void write_characters(const CharType *s, std::size_t length) = 0;
4255  virtual ~output_adapter_protocol() = default;
4256  };
4257 
4259  template <typename CharType>
4260  using output_adapter_t = std::shared_ptr<output_adapter_protocol<CharType>>;
4261 
4263  template <typename CharType>
4264  class output_vector_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType> {
4265  public:
4266  explicit output_vector_adapter(std::vector<CharType> &vec) : v(vec) {
4267  }
4268 
4269  void write_character(CharType c) override {
4270  v.push_back(c);
4271  }
4272 
4273  void write_characters(const CharType *s, std::size_t length) override {
4274  std::copy(s, s + length, std::back_inserter(v));
4275  }
4276 
4277  private:
4278  std::vector<CharType> &v;
4279  };

4287 
4288  void write_character(CharType c) override {
4289  stream.put(c);
4290  }
4291 
4292  void write_characters(const CharType *s, std::size_t length) override {
4293  stream.write(s, static_cast<std::streamsize>(length));
4294  }
4295 
4296  private:
4297  std::basic_ostream<CharType> &stream;
4298  };

4312  str.append(s, length);
4313  }
4314 
4315  private:

4317  };

4455  static constexpr bool little_endianess(int num = 1) noexcept {
4456  return (*reinterpret_cast<char *>(&num) == 1);
4457  }
4458 
4459  private:
4465  BasicJsonType parse_cbor_internal(const bool get_char = true) {
4466  switch (get_char ? get() : current) {
4467  // EOF
4468  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
4469  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(110, chars_read, "unexpected end of input"));
4470 
4471  // Integer 0x00..0x17 (0..23)
4472  case 0x00:
4473  case 0x01:
4474  case 0x02:
4475  case 0x03:
4476  case 0x04:
4477  case 0x05:
4478  case 0x06:
4479  case 0x07:
4480  case 0x08:
4481  case 0x09:
4482  case 0x0A:
4483  case 0x0B:
4484  case 0x0C:
4485  case 0x0D:
4486  case 0x0E:
4487  case 0x0F:
4488  case 0x10:
4489  case 0x11:
4490  case 0x12:
4491  case 0x13:
4492  case 0x14:
4493  case 0x15:
4494  case 0x16:
4495  case 0x17:
4496  return static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(current);
4497 
4498  case 0x18: // Unsigned integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
4499  return get_number<uint8_t>();
4500 
4501  case 0x19: // Unsigned integer (two-byte uint16_t follows)
4502  return get_number<uint16_t>();
4503 
4504  case 0x1A: // Unsigned integer (four-byte uint32_t follows)
4505  return get_number<uint32_t>();
4506 
4507  case 0x1B: // Unsigned integer (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
4508  return get_number<uint64_t>();
4509 
4510  // Negative integer -1-0x00..-1-0x17 (-1..-24)
4511  case 0x20:
4512  case 0x21:
4513  case 0x22:
4514  case 0x23:
4515  case 0x24:
4516  case 0x25:
4517  case 0x26:
4518  case 0x27:
4519  case 0x28:
4520  case 0x29:
4521  case 0x2A:
4522  case 0x2B:
4523  case 0x2C:
4524  case 0x2D:
4525  case 0x2E:
4526  case 0x2F:
4527  case 0x30:
4528  case 0x31:
4529  case 0x32:
4530  case 0x33:
4531  case 0x34:
4532  case 0x35:
4533  case 0x36:
4534  case 0x37:
4535  return static_cast<int8_t>(0x20 - 1 - current);
4536 
4537  case 0x38: // Negative integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
4538  {
4539  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - get_number<uint8_t>();
4540  }
4541 
4542  case 0x39: // Negative integer -1-n (two-byte uint16_t follows)
4543  {
4544  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - get_number<uint16_t>();
4545  }
4546 
4547  case 0x3A: // Negative integer -1-n (four-byte uint32_t follows)
4548  {
4549  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - get_number<uint32_t>();
4550  }
4551 
4552  case 0x3B: // Negative integer -1-n (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
4553  {
4554  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - static_cast<number_integer_t>(get_number<uint64_t>());
4555  }
4556 
4557  // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
4558  case 0x60:
4559  case 0x61:
4560  case 0x62:
4561  case 0x63:
4562  case 0x64:
4563  case 0x65:
4564  case 0x66:
4565  case 0x67:
4566  case 0x68:
4567  case 0x69:
4568  case 0x6A:
4569  case 0x6B:
4570  case 0x6C:
4571  case 0x6D:
4572  case 0x6E:
4573  case 0x6F:
4574  case 0x70:
4575  case 0x71:
4576  case 0x72:
4577  case 0x73:
4578  case 0x74:
4579  case 0x75:
4580  case 0x76:
4581  case 0x77:
4582  case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
4583  case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
4584  case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
4585  case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
4586  case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
4587  {
4588  return get_cbor_string();
4589  }
4590 
4591  // array (0x00..0x17 data items follow)
4592  case 0x80:
4593  case 0x81:
4594  case 0x82:
4595  case 0x83:
4596  case 0x84:
4597  case 0x85:
4598  case 0x86:
4599  case 0x87:
4600  case 0x88:
4601  case 0x89:
4602  case 0x8A:
4603  case 0x8B:
4604  case 0x8C:
4605  case 0x8D:
4606  case 0x8E:
4607  case 0x8F:
4608  case 0x90:
4609  case 0x91:
4610  case 0x92:
4611  case 0x93:
4612  case 0x94:
4613  case 0x95:
4614  case 0x96:
4615  case 0x97: {
4616  return get_cbor_array(current & 0x1F);
4617  }
4618 
4619  case 0x98: // array (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
4620  {
4621  return get_cbor_array(get_number<uint8_t>());
4622  }
4623 
4624  case 0x99: // array (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
4625  {
4626  return get_cbor_array(get_number<uint16_t>());
4627  }
4628 
4629  case 0x9A: // array (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
4630  {
4631  return get_cbor_array(get_number<uint32_t>());
4632  }
4633 
4634  case 0x9B: // array (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
4635  {
4636  return get_cbor_array(get_number<uint64_t>());
4637  }
4638 
4639  case 0x9F: // array (indefinite length)
4640  {
4641  BasicJsonType result = value_t::array;
4642  while (get() != 0xFF) {
4643  result.push_back(parse_cbor_internal(false));
4644  }
4645  return result;
4646  }
4647 
4648  // map (0x00..0x17 pairs of data items follow)
4649  case 0xA0:
4650  case 0xA1:
4651  case 0xA2:
4652  case 0xA3:
4653  case 0xA4:
4654  case 0xA5:
4655  case 0xA6:
4656  case 0xA7:
4657  case 0xA8:
4658  case 0xA9:
4659  case 0xAA:
4660  case 0xAB:
4661  case 0xAC:
4662  case 0xAD:
4663  case 0xAE:
4664  case 0xAF:
4665  case 0xB0:
4666  case 0xB1:
4667  case 0xB2:
4668  case 0xB3:
4669  case 0xB4:
4670  case 0xB5:
4671  case 0xB6:
4672  case 0xB7: {
4673  return get_cbor_object(current & 0x1F);
4674  }
4675 
4676  case 0xB8: // map (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
4677  {
4678  return get_cbor_object(get_number<uint8_t>());
4679  }
4680 
4681  case 0xB9: // map (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
4682  {
4683  return get_cbor_object(get_number<uint16_t>());
4684  }
4685 
4686  case 0xBA: // map (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
4687  {
4688  return get_cbor_object(get_number<uint32_t>());
4689  }
4690 
4691  case 0xBB: // map (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
4692  {
4693  return get_cbor_object(get_number<uint64_t>());
4694  }
4695 
4696  case 0xBF: // map (indefinite length)
4697  {
4698  BasicJsonType result = value_t::object;
4699  while (get() != 0xFF) {
4700  auto key = get_cbor_string();
4701  result[key] = parse_cbor_internal();
4702  }
4703  return result;
4704  }
4705 
4706  case 0xF4: // false
4707  {
4708  return false;
4709  }
4710 
4711  case 0xF5: // true
4712  {
4713  return true;
4714  }
4715 
4716  case 0xF6: // null
4717  {
4718  return value_t::null;
4719  }
4720 
4721  case 0xF9: // Half-Precision Float (two-byte IEEE 754)
4722  {
4723  const int byte1 = get();
4724  unexpect_eof();
4725  const int byte2 = get();
4726  unexpect_eof();
4727 
4728  // code from RFC 7049, Appendix D, Figure 3:
4729  // As half-precision floating-point numbers were only added
4730  // to IEEE 754 in 2008, today's programming platforms often
4731  // still only have limited support for them. It is very
4732  // easy to include at least decoding support for them even
4733  // without such support. An example of a small decoder for
4734  // half-precision floating-point numbers in the C language
4735  // is shown in Fig. 3.
4736  const int half = (byte1 << 8) + byte2;
4737  const int exp = (half >> 10) & 0x1F;
4738  const int mant = half & 0x3FF;
4739  double val;
4740  if (exp == 0) {
4741  val = std::ldexp(mant, -24);
4742  } else if (exp != 31) {
4743  val = std::ldexp(mant + 1024, exp - 25);
4744  } else {
4745  val = (mant == 0) ? std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity() : std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
4746  }
4747  return (half & 0x8000) != 0 ? -val : val;
4748  }
4749 
4750  case 0xFA: // Single-Precision Float (four-byte IEEE 754)
4751  {
4752  return get_number<float>();
4753  }
4754 
4755  case 0xFB: // Double-Precision Float (eight-byte IEEE 754)
4756  {
4757  return get_number<double>();
4758  }
4759 
4760  default: // anything else (0xFF is handled inside the other types)
4761  {
4762  std::stringstream ss;
4763  ss << std::setw(2) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
4764  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(112, chars_read, "error reading CBOR; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
4765  }
4766  }
4767  }

5115  int get_ignore_noop() {
5116  do {
5117  get();

5122 
5123  /*
5124  @brief read a number from the input
5125 
5126  @tparam NumberType the type of the number
5127 
5128  @return number of type @a NumberType
5129 
5130  @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because
5131  bytes in CBOR and MessagePack are stored in network order (big
5132  endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
5133 
5134  @throw parse_error.110 if input has less than `sizeof(NumberType)` bytes
5135  */
5136  template <typename NumberType>
5137  NumberType get_number() {
5138  // step 1: read input into array with system's byte order
5139  std::array<uint8_t, sizeof(NumberType)> vec;
5140  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(NumberType); ++i) {
5141  get();
5142  unexpect_eof();
5143 
5144  // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
5145  if (is_little_endian) {
5146  vec[sizeof(NumberType) - i - 1] = static_cast<uint8_t>(current);
5147  } else {
5148  vec[i] = static_cast<uint8_t>(current); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
5149  }
5150  }
5151 
5152  // step 2: convert array into number of type T and return
5153  NumberType result;
5154  std::memcpy(&result, vec.data(), sizeof(NumberType));
5155  return result;
5156  }
5157 
5171  template <typename NumberType>
5172  string_t get_string(const NumberType len) {
5173  string_t result;
5174  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(result), len, [this]() {
5175  get();
5176  unexpect_eof();
5177  return static_cast<char>(current);
5178  });
5179  return result;
5180  }
5181 
5194  string_t get_cbor_string() {
5195  unexpect_eof();
5196 
5197  switch (current) {
5198  // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
5199  case 0x60:
5200  case 0x61:
5201  case 0x62:
5202  case 0x63:
5203  case 0x64:
5204  case 0x65:
5205  case 0x66:
5206  case 0x67:
5207  case 0x68:
5208  case 0x69:
5209  case 0x6A:
5210  case 0x6B:
5211  case 0x6C:
5212  case 0x6D:
5213  case 0x6E:
5214  case 0x6F:
5215  case 0x70:
5216  case 0x71:
5217  case 0x72:
5218  case 0x73:
5219  case 0x74:
5220  case 0x75:
5221  case 0x76:
5222  case 0x77: {
5223  return get_string(current & 0x1F);
5224  }
5225 
5226  case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
5227  {
5228  return get_string(get_number<uint8_t>());
5229  }
5230 
5231  case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
5232  {
5233  return get_string(get_number<uint16_t>());
5234  }
5235 
5236  case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
5237  {
5238  return get_string(get_number<uint32_t>());
5239  }
5240 
5241  case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
5242  {
5243  return get_string(get_number<uint64_t>());
5244  }
5245 
5246  case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
5247  {
5248  string_t result;
5249  while (get() != 0xFF) {
5250  unexpect_eof();
5251  result.push_back(static_cast<char>(current));
5252  }
5253  return result;
5254  }
5255 
5256  default: {
5257  std::stringstream ss;
5258  ss << std::setw(2) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
5259  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(113, chars_read, "expected a CBOR string; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
5260  }
5261  }
5262  }
5263 
5264  template <typename NumberType>
5265  BasicJsonType get_cbor_array(const NumberType len) {
5266  BasicJsonType result = value_t::array;
5267  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(*result.m_value.array), len, [this]() { return parse_cbor_internal(); });
5268  return result;
5269  }

5271  template <typename NumberType>
5272  BasicJsonType get_cbor_object(const NumberType len) {
5273  BasicJsonType result = value_t::object;
5274  std::generate_n(std::inserter(*result.m_value.object, result.m_value.object->end()), len, [this]() {
5275  get();
5276  auto key = get_cbor_string();
5277  auto val = parse_cbor_internal();
5278  return std::make_pair(std::move(key), std::move(val));
5279  });
5280  return result;
5281  }
